      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAWBOURNE CALI (2) is a talented type who skirted wide from an outside draw and crossed down to the inside, leading throughout to win (30.46) at this track in Grade 4/5 over 525m. Form at this distance is sound. Recorded the quickest time on the card last start. Well placed and will be tough to beat. SANTINO KADE (1) was popular in betting last start but disappointed when 6 lengths away in eighth (23.01). Was in the money the start prior. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Has ability and is one of the better chances. ELITE DOM (5) is progressing well with another good run last time, placing (30.53) at this track. Solid record here at the distance winning three races. Deserves a win and gets his chance. BACARDI GIRL (3) hit the frame latest (34.61) when third at Angle Park in a Grade 4/5. Already a winner from this draw.",
